ion but also exceptional literary distinction, and is essential reading for all students and lovers of Stravinsky.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMusiciansvBiography. 4ahistory of music. 4amodern classical music history. 4amusic theory. 4amusic. 7aMUSIC / History & Criticism.2bisacsh1 aCraft, Robert, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z97831106353480 cprintz978052033461840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520334625?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520334625423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520334625/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles